@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Laplace Manual -------------------------------------------------- Projects -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "Usage" "Projects"
@{U}3.11) Projects@{UU}

   Projects are usually placed in the @{B}Projects@{UB} directory.

   Laplace uses now a binary file  format. This offers the new possibility  to
load a project in (almost) exactly the  same state as you saved it,  including
all results,  definitions and  options. You  can enable  this feature  in  the
@{"preferences" LINK "Preferences"} window.

   If you still want to  import a project in  your favorite ASCII editor,  you
can use the @{B}Export...@{UB} function from the @{B}Project@{UB} menu. This will create a  file
only with the input lines,  each one seperated by a  blank line. You can  also
@{B}Import...@{UB} such an ASCII file.


@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}------------------------------------------------------------------ ® by P!\K -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}
@ENDNODE
